main event: A sighting of a circular object with no discernable features was reported on 31 January 1955.
interesting points: The object was first thought to be a balloon but appeared to move against the wind,The object was observed by the Air Force at a height of 17,000 feet, estimated to be between 45,000 and 50,000 feet,The length of the observation was 6 minutes,The motion picture film taken was of poor quality with no discernible features on the object,The report concluded it was probably a balloon due to insufficient data.
sighted object: circular object with no discernable features
